President Muhammadu Buhari on Tuesday signed the 2023 appropriation bill of N21.83 trillion into law. Buhari signed the budget at the council chamber of the presidential villa, Abuja. Among those present at the signing are Senate President Ahmad Lawan; Femi Gbajabiamila, speaker of the house of representatives; Zainab Ahmad, finance minster; Boss Mustapha, secretary to the government of the federation (SGF), and James Faleke, chairman of the committee on finance. Below are photos.        